**Post 1**

URL: https://www.linkedin.com/posts/ethanls_ai-is-probabilistic-random-measurable-activity-7450151017423417344-65cH

Content:
AI is probabilistic.

Not random.
Not deterministic.

Probabilistic.

That means every output is a distribution of possible answers — not a single truth.

So when you evaluate AI, you shouldn’t ask:
“Is this correct?”

You should ask:
“What’s the likelihood this is correct?”

This shift changes everything:

How you prompt
How you evaluate outputs
How you build systems on top of AI

Because if you treat AI like a database,

…it will fail you.

But if you treat it like a probability engine,

…it becomes incredibly powerful.

